ichardson  ."]},{"name":"Richerson","meanings":["Probably an altered form of   Richardson   or perhaps a patronymic from   Richer  ."]},{"name":"Richard","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Emile, Jacques, Andre, Marcel, Pierre, Leonce, Normand, Camille, Lucien, Gilles, Henri.","English, French, West Indian (mainly Haiti), German, and Dutch: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful)’ + <i>hard</i> ‘hardy, brave, strong’. The Middle English forms were <i>Richard</i> and <i>Rikard</i>, respectively Parisian Old French and Old Picard pronunciations of the ancient Germanic name. Middle English <i>Rikard</i> gives rise to the pet form   Rick  , whilst <i>Richard</i> has given the pet forms   Richie   and   Rich  . Both produced rhyming pet forms,   Dick   and   Hick   for <i>Rikard</i> and   Hitch   for <i>Richard</i>.","History: The LA Richard families are mainly descended from Acadian refugees in the second half of the 18th century. — This surname is listed in the register of Huguenot ancestors recognized by the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Richeson","meanings":["Probably an altered form of   Richardson  , but compare   Richerson  ."]},{"name":"Ritson","meanings":["English:","variant of <b>Richson</b>, a shortened form of   Richardson  . The name may sometimes have been confused with or assimilated to   Rushton  .","in southern England perhaps a habitational name from Ritson, in Halwell (Devon)."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph Richardson was born on 11 July 1455, in Westmill, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Bedo ap Richard, was 25 and his mother, Mawd Verch Levan Frychan, was 30. He had at least 1 son with Jeanne Michiell. He died in 1520, in Is-sur-Tille, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France, at the age of 65."},"et":{"2 July 1455–1520":"11. juuli 1455–1520","1455–1520":"1455–1520","1462–1503":"1462–1503","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1503":"1503","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1520":"1520","1430":"1430","1540":"1540","1462":"1462","1480":"1480","2 July 1455":"11. juuli 1455","Westmill, Hertfordshire, , England":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Westmill, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Is-sur-Tille, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Is-sur-Tille, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"2 July 1455–1520":"11. heinäkuuta 1455–1520","1455–1520":"1455–1520","1462–1503":"1462–1503","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1430–Male":"1430–Kuollut","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1503":"1503","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1520":"1520","1430":"1430","1540":"1540","1462":"1462","1480":"1480","2 July 1455":"11. heinäkuuta 1455","Westmill, Hertfordshire, , England":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Westmill, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Is-sur-Tille, Côte-d'Or, Burgundy, France":"Is-sur-Tille, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Ranska"},"fr":{"2 July 1455–1520":"11 juillet 1455–1520","1455–1520":"1455–1520","1462–1503":"1462–1503","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1430–Male":"1430–Décédé","1425–Female":"1425–Décédée","1503":"1503","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1520":"1520","1430":"1430","1540":"1540","1462":"14